Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente,
~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings),
then drain. (Keep empty pot handy for Step 4.)

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Place between two
large pieces of #plastic wrap{} and pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{}
until chicken is about 1/2 inch thick. Season with @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Place @flour{1%tablespoon} on a #plate{}. Working one piece at a time, press
chicken into flour until fully coated, then shake off any excess.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.
Transfer to a #cutting board{}. TIP: Cook in batches if necessary; lower heat
if chicken browns too quickly.

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in #pot{} used for pasta
over medium heat. Add garlic, half the lemon zest, and a pinch of
@?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (big pinch for 4) if desired. Cook, stirring,
until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce} and juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges
for 4). Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add drained spaghetti and @peas{4%ounce} to pot with sauce and toss until
evenly coated. TIP: If needed, stir in pasta cooking water a splash at a time
until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Slice chicken crosswise if desired.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and top with chicken. Sprinkle with remaining
lemon zest and a pinch of chili flakes if desired. Serve with remaining lemon
wedges on the side.